President Muhammadu Buhari has commiserated with leader of Afenifere, Pa Reuben Fasoranti, on the death of his daughter, Mrs Funke Olakunrin. Quoted in a statement by his spokesperson, Femi Adesina, the president also directed security agencies to swing into action and bring the hoodlums to justice in the shortest possible time. The deceased was reportedly shot on Friday along the Kajola-Ore road, in Ondo State, by those the police described as armed robbers. OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. CLICK HERE TO KNOW MORE The President prayed that God will comfort Pa Fasoranti and give him the fortitude to bear the grievous loss. Again, Yoruba leaders renew demand for restructuring Obasanjo visits Afenifere leader, Fasoranti in Akure after 20 years Afenifere hosts Obasanjo, supports change of govt in 2019 Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin